# Stronghold® Brand Guidelines

All outputs must be brand-compliant. Always use the ® symbol with Stronghold.

## Colors

- **Main Blue:** #0B2993 (primary headlines, CTAs, key brand elements)
- **Contrast Blue:** #0075FF (interactive elements, emphasis)
- **Core Black:** #060810 (body text, dark backgrounds)
- **Green:** #1CB06C | **Yellow:** #F6DE3F | **Red:** #DC2307
- **Royal Blue:** #3C70B7 | **Sky Blue:** #42A2DA
- Never use colors outside the approved palette

## Typography

- **Primary font:** Proxima Nova (fallback: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif)
- H1–H4: Bold | H5–H6: Semibold | Body: Regular
- Documents fallback: Helvetica (never Calibri)

## Voice & Tone

- Professional yet approachable, confident but not arrogant, clear and direct
- Use active voice, concise sentences, lead with benefits
- Use: strong, secure, reliable, trusted, innovative, modern, efficient
- Avoid: slang, hyperbole ("best ever," "revolutionary"), competitor references

## Logo Usage

**Logo repo:** https://github.com/strongholdpay/Stronghold-Branding-Kit-PUBLIC-FOR-ALL

Embed the Blue logo in markdown:
```
![Stronghold®](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/strongholdpay/Stronghold-Branding-Kit-PUBLIC-FOR-ALL/main/Stronghold%20Logos%20-%20March%202022/Blue/Stronghold%20Logo%20Type%20Blue.svg)
```

- **Light backgrounds:** Blue (preferred) or Black logo
- **Dark backgrounds:** White logo
- **Partner materials:** "Powered by Stronghold" variant
- Include logo in document headers or footers
- Never distort, recolor, or add effects to logos

